         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">

<ab><lb n="1"/>  <g ref="#scroll"/>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἀρτεμίδωρος">Ἀρτεμίδωρος</name>  <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπολλωνίου</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Περείτας">Πε<lb n="3" break="no"/>ρείτου</name></persName></persName></persName> <g ref="#stop"/> <w lemma="στεφανηφορέω">στεφανηφορή <lb n="4" break="no"/>σας</w>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Κότας">Κότας</name></persName> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκεν</w> <lb n="5"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">Δήμῳ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὴν</w> <w lemma="εἰκών">εἰκόνα</w> <g ref="#scroll"/><lb n="6"/>  <space extent="1" unit="line" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Artemidoros son of Apollonios the son of Pereitas former stephanephorus: Kotas set up the image for the People.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Kotas might be a further name of Artemidoros; but the phrasing suggests that he is a separate person. If so the image was presumably of Artemidoros.</p>
         </div>
